where c = Ä¯x/Ä¯t is defined as the lattice speed, Ä¯x is the length of lattice. wi is the weight coefficients given by w0 =
4/9, wi = 1/9 for i = 1,2,3,4, and wi = 1/16 for i = 5,6,7,8. Once fi (x, t) is known, the macroscopic blood density È¡ and
